        <section id="fd">
            <h2>Fixed Deposit (FD)</h2>
            <p>A Fixed Deposit (FD) allows you to invest a lump sum amount for a fixed tenure at a predetermined interest rate.</p>
            <h3>Key Features:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Interest Rate: Fixed for the entire tenure.</li>
                <li>Tenure: Ranges from 7 days to 10 years.</li>
                <li>Premature Withdrawal: Allowed with a penalty.</li>
                <li>Taxation: Subject to tax; TDS deducted if interest exceeds ₹40,000 (₹50,000 for senior citizens).</li>
                <li>Security: Backed by the government up to ₹5 lakhs.</li>
                <li>Flexibility: Available in different options like cumulative and non-cumulative interest payouts.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Benefits:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Risk-free investment with guaranteed returns.</li>
                <li>High liquidity with premature withdrawal options.</li>
                <li>Easy to manage and set up.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Interest Calculation Formula:</h3>
            <p><strong>Interest = Principal × Rate × Time</strong></p>
        </section>

        <section id="rd">
            <h2>Recurring Deposit (RD)</h2>
            <p>An RD allows regular monthly investments for a fixed tenure with a fixed interest rate.</p>
            <h3>Key Features:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Regular Investment: Fixed monthly deposits.</li>
                <li>Tenure: Ranges from 6 months to 10 years.</li>
                <li>Premature Withdrawal: Allowed with penalties.</li>
                <li>Taxation: Interest earned is taxable; TDS applies.</li>
                <li>Discipline: Encourages regular savings habits.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Benefits:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Low initial deposit requirements.</li>
                <li>Option to automate deposits through ECS/NACH.</li>
                <li>Flexible tenure for planning short-term and long-term goals.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Interest Calculation Formula:</h3>
            <p><strong>Interest = P × n × (n+1) × R / 2400</strong></p>
        </section>

